# Ignore file for the @cloudpdf/server image build.
#
# The image is built with the repo root as the build context
# (`docker build -f ee/server/Dockerfile .`). BuildKit honours the
# `<dockerfile>.dockerignore` that sits next to the Dockerfile, so this
# file scopes the context for the server image without affecting any
# other build. (A plain `ee/server/.dockerignore` would only apply when
# the build context itself is `ee/server`, which it is not here.)
#
# Goal: keep the context small + deterministic. We deliberately keep all
# workspace `package.json` files (turbo prune needs the full workspace
# graph) and only drop build outputs, caches, VCS, and the giant native
# submodules.

# Dependencies + build outputs (regenerated inside the image)
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/.turbo
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# Framework build outputs that also contain stray nested package.json
# copies (these break `turbo prune` workspace discovery if included).
**/.next
**/.svelte-kit
**/.vercel

# VCS + tooling state
.git
**/.git
.github
.changeset
.husky
.claude
.cursor
.vscode
.idea
.DS_Store

# Native source submodules (huge; not needed - we fetch a pinned
# prebuilt libpdfium and compile only the small N-API addon).
packages/pdfium/pdfium-src
packages/pdf-runtime/runtime-src

# pdf-runtime local build caches (regenerated by build:target).
packages/pdf-runtime/build/build
packages/pdf-runtime/build/cache
packages/pdf-runtime/build/generated
packages/pdf-runtime/build/libpdfium
packages/pdf-runtime/build/local-artifacts
packages/pdf-runtime/build/local-staging

# Docs / site source (not needed to build the server; kept out of context
# weight - their package.json still ships so the workspace graph resolves).
website/.next
website/out
ee/website/.next
ee/website/out

# Test/coverage noise
**/coverage
**/.vitest
